column1: Hello, this is Savita Vishwanathan. I've been living in Mumbai since birth. But I also want my marriage to be one based on mutual love, respect and lots of fun (unlike what most marriages turn out to be these days). Which is why the search for the right partner is so very crucial to me and I'd like to spend sometime knowing you before making any decision. What am I looking for in my partner? - well, someone who's smart, is well spoken and has a good persona...understands relations...believes in love...wants to stay by his partner's side through thick and thin....believes in having a conversation...has a good sense of humor! Someone who shares my values and believes in being a friend first and then a partner. Life is not easy, but its fun to share tough times with someone who loves and respects you.Communication is key, so someone who is fluent in English and Hindi would really help (considering my malayalam is just awesome ;) ))...If you think I am what you are looking for in your partner. About me: 
Outgoing, optimistic, highly personable.  Believe in adapting the best of global and Indian values.

I have always interacted with people from various walks of life. And it continually enriches me.

I firmly believe that family and friends are our anchors and it's essential to support, help and encourage everyone around us to lead a better life.

I believe there is a spiritual guide for us, and it encompasses the religion we follow and the deities we worship. 

I'm fond of books, advertising, brands, movies, music, culture and travel. I collect vintage ads and have a collection of books, music and movies.

I've travelled across most parts of India and some places abroad in childhood days. Plan and hope to see much more of the world.

I love exploring the cultural nuances that exist around and beyond us.

Educational Qualifications:
1) MMS (Master of Management Studies, Silver Medalist). 2) B.Com (awarded Best Degree College Student) from University of  Mumbai. 
3) Schooled in a Bandra convent school.

Professional:
Associate Director in a MNC advertising agency. Role - strategy planning for digital brand campaigns. Annual income - INR 10+ lacs.
Aim to balance home and work life in the future.,"Expectations for Spouse:
Education and professional outlook are key. Post-graduate and above would enable us to have similar outlooks.
Should be able to balance his professional focus and be family-oriented. Should look forward to raising family.

A sociable person/extrovert would perhaps be more compatible with my personality type. Someone who share some of my interests and passions such as traveling and exploring interesting life experiences.
I'm not an avid sports fan and don't subscribe to the national fascination for cricket.
Would also prefer a non-smoker. ","Father - Formerly, Chief Engineer in the Merchant Navy (SCI) and has been in offshore shipping since 1990.
Mother - M.Sc., B. Ed., taught for a couple of years in schools like Apeejay and Kendriya Vidyalaya. Continues to tutor children.
Younger brother -  B.A. (Economics), works in a media agency.
I?m thankful for being raised in a family where education and careers have been of paramount importance. We have had a well-rounded upbringing with rich experiences. We've been in Bombay since 1983.

Our extended families, maternal and paternal, reside across Gurgaon, Panchkula and throughout Northern India. column1:
With CS, LLB , M'COM, M.A degrees to add to my extrinsic persona, prefer a perfect balance of Sensitivity and Sensibility.. at right time & right situation.. at the intrinsic layers of my identity.

We live not just for us but for the people who have made us what we are!

My deep rooted desire, to make my marriage. the most cherished gift of my life, wherein  bestowed with a thoughtful and loving soul mate, we work towards a superb partnership, of constructively contributing.. to the happiness of people around us and in turn discover the best in each other.


What Am I Looking For?

Simplicity. Respect. Clarity in thoughts n speech and purity in deeds. All this with a realization..that we all are imperfect with a goal towards perfection.

Education & Values are eternal gifts that never fade away with times.And for the rest of the talents and skills , have childlike curiosity to learn & imbibe them...with a terrible bad luck in sports, not giving up though! Perhaps it is testimony to the fact that I am a perfect citizen of Planet Venus minus that macho abilities of residents of Mars!!,"Balances Idealism with Pragmatism at right times. Absolutely Self Made & Self Respecting.
Brilliance   determined either by good education or by excellence in chosen goal of life.

Trusts the choices made by the better half, as far as decisions pertaining to her life goes. I have many a times back tracked my ambitions to the needs of my loved ones.. & my sensitivities dominate my intellect, to continue to do the same, for my future family. Might choose to work for our happiness, or might sacrifice work, to be with them, for our strong bonding.Am unpredictable in this regard..excuses n acceptances!
Let the good old hindi film ideas of true love and eternal romance be part of my married life.","Close Knit. Loving but keen on discipline.
Well Reputed, joint family business.

Firm belief in Simplicity and dislike for undue sophistication. Prefer Self Purification above rituals. Grown up daughters , as daughters and not as sons, but educated them taught them to be courageous.. not just degree wise, but to become wise to take the best course of life, to uphold family dignity & self respect.",30 to 35,28 Mar 1980,11:10:00,India,Mumbai,Average,Doesn't Matter,0 brothers ,Patel,,,Institute of Company Secretaries of India (ICSI),Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,CS (Company Secretary),"33 yrs, 5ft 2in,

column1:
Finding it difficult to jot down about myself in few words lest it would look like a CV.. am quite patient, level-headed, optimistic, loyal, easily adapt & adjust to surroundings.. a fun loving person who absolutely loves food, nature, mountains, trekking, travel, cooking, gardening, cinema, theater, music, dance, photography, books, tea, conversations, parks, postcards, colours, painting, blogging, going for long walks.. a bit old fashioned at heart too who still loves writing long letters to close friends in this age of instant communication or holding a real book in my hand over the unknown joy of owning a 'kindle' or any of the latest gadgets or technology for that matter.. the old world charm of many a things continue to fascinate me.. i am all for minimalistic and sustainable living.

I do believe in god and inherent goodness in people but not so much in religion and rituals (and this includes matching horoscopes as well).. am very secular, independent and liberal with a live-n-let live attitude.

My current role work-wise is that of a content manager (for a US based firm into advanced education and career services).. i will continue with this role in case i decide to relocate elsewhere post marriage.

Do write in if interested and wish you all the very best in your search for someone to live, grow, explore n enjoy the rest of your life with :-),"Someone who's optimistic, independent, witty, sociable, broadminded, non-judgemental, loves outdoors, nature.. matches my frequency in terms of values and has interests other than just job and career! i strongly believe there is so much more to life.. someone i can share many a good conversations with and explore each other in the journey ahead.. who will help me grow as a person (& vice versa).. someone simple, warm, loving n a romantic at heart.. compatibility matters to me much more than the other factors.. it's alright if we don't share all the interests/thoughts/hobbies listed above (and an absolute delight if we actually do share a few! :-) but i would love to have my space and individuality to pursue my own interests and vice versa.

i remember reading this line somewhere, sometime ago which i could relate to in the context of marriage as well - ""Love is not about being with someone who can make you feel complete, but someone with whom you can share your incompleteness...""

Good luck and peace!","A small family of four - Papa retired from BARC, Mumbai 3 years ago and Aai has been looking after home for past 28 yrs.. my only younger sister is working as a Corporate Planner with a reputed Tours n Travel Group in Mumbai.. they mean a lot to me.. i am who am today only because of their unconditional love n support which keeps me sane, happy n at peace with myself n the world in general :-)",31 to 36,29 Dec 1979,,India,Mumbai,Average,Average,0 brothers ,Bhandari,,,,Wheatish ,Doesn't Matter,Self,B.Com (Commerce),"33 yrs, 5ft 5in,

As far as horoscope goes, we believe that the mental understanding, mutual respect is more important than meeting of the nakshatras and gunanks. Horoscope matching is only to ensure that there is some degree of compatibility but that should not become the only decisive factor.

The reason why human beings are different from animals is because they are well cultured. This is the basic thing that I look in a person when I meet him. This criterion has always been very successful for me to judge people. I am a very well cultured person myself and that is what I also appreciate in people. 
I have been the same since childhood. My parents inculcated this in me and I am very thankful to my parents for that. I am sure this will always remain in me because I respect myself for this nature of mine. 
I am a Business Analyst in an MNC and I like my job. I dona??t crib about my work like many other people do. I would like to continue with my work and grow in the same field but if in future, I have some problems managing my work and my family I can leave working. 
My mother is a homemaker and my father is the Vice president in a software company. I find my parents the best people on earth and I appreciate their love and affection towards me. I pray to god that they make me efficient enough that I can give them whatever they expect from me. 
My school life was quiet smooth and after that, I did B tech from Wadia College in Pune. 
I have a very creative nature and I like doing things that are out of the box. I like to decorate flowers and watch movies.,"He should be well settled. This will make him very eligible for me, as settled people do not have the tension and pressure at that level. He will himself feel very relaxed if he is settled. Also, I dona??t want to struggle after marriage and want to live a peaceful life.

I am strictly against the habit of smoking cigarettes and consuming alcohol. I think these things just create nuisance in the family. They not only spoil the heath of the people who are consuming it but also harm those who remain close to them.

When two people marry each other, they not only have to have a relationship with each other but also with each othera??s families. I hope the man I get married to has a good family so that I can adjust with them and love them like my own family.

I am very lovable and caring therefore, I will expect the same from my partner too. This way we can become a very compatible couple. I am sure our relationship will be very strong and long lasting if we reciprocate the good feelings that we have for each other.
I respect the idea of a good friend in a husband. I will love it if he becomes a good friend of mine as I will feel more connected to him this way.

My partner should have good understanding of family, relationships and big heart for sharing with others. I'm very simple, ambitious, hardworking person. I'm already successful professionally but down to earth as I know 'Sky is the limit.' I'm looking for a partner who shares these qualities.

column1:
We are straight out of Bride and Prejudice ? a Sikh family, four sisters, a gorgeous mother and, of course, the eternal search for ?suitable boys?. The youngest sisters are twins, and my sister for who we have posted this ad, is one of the twins. 

GROWING UP: Dad served and retired as a Colonel in the Indian Army, and we grew up all over the country ? including big cities like Delhi and Kolkata, and on huge farm houses in smaller cities like Lucknow and Meerut. The summers of our childhood were spent at our grandparents? village ringed by emerald green fields in the Punjab. Or motoring up the highest bridge in the world and picnicking by the Indus in Ladakh. 

She studied at convent schools wherever Dad was posted at the time and then, in Class VIII, the twins went to study in a boarding school in the hills near Chandigarh. They insist they spent the best time of their lives there and frankly speaking, we are all quite jealous of their large, close-knit, persisting circle of friends. 

She studied MBA in Human Resources at an Army institute in that fun student town, Pune. While others partied, my sister worked her ass off. She can be the serious, committed sort. We all believe that the partying would have done her good. 

WORK: The serious, committed, focused person that she is, she has recruited and hired for brand new branches for an MNC bank. We have never seen her at work, but we won?t be surprised if her colleagues call her the Rock. She is currently in Pune working for IBM India.
HER: Of the four sisters, she?s brought home the biggest bonus, she bakes the best cakes, and she has the most beautiful eyes. She is quite boringly untiring about the way she helps her parents; the other twin can be quite a brat. She has bought her mom diamonds, she has let her twin raid her wardrobe. She, frankly speaking, needs to learn how to push back. She could also do better while making life decisions. She is an introvert, an ironing and neat freak,"YOU: One school of family thought, which believes in the incredible connection between the twins, says it would be nice for the two to be in the same country. So, we would love to hear from a??suitable boysa?? living in the States.

Another school of thought says the location does not matter, as long as the guy is a renaissance man, living in one of the big cities in India where my sister can find a job to match her education and experience.

Either way, we are looking for a man from any religion, state in India. It does not matter whether you are from Kerala or Orissa. You need to have had a good education, you work in the professional services, you have promise and a vision for how you want to shape your career. You believe in yourself, you care for your family, you are liberal, you respect women and their choices. You are prepared to work with my sister on your relationship, you do not already have a mental mould of a partner into which you want to pour my sister into. Lastly, and most importantly, you do not have a temper.

If you fit the bill, and our sister approves of you, we would love to welcome you in our family..",,32 to 36,30 Dec 1979,06:30:00,India,Jalandhar,Slim,Doesn't Matter,0 brothers ,Sikh - Jat,,Rest of Punjab,"ILS, Pune",Wheatish ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MBA/PGDM,"33 yrs, 5ft 3in,

column1:
What you see is what you get. I am a straight forward, honest, hardworking single woman. I work as a Project Manager in the IT department of my company. When I moved to Boston a couple years ago, I immediately fell in love with the city, its crooked streets and the Charles River. Both Cambridge and Boston remind me very much of my hometown in Mumbai.
Sky Diving has been my most memorable adventure till date and I will soon be going for a flight lesson.
I also enjoy traveling, although it has been very limited lately. Just got back from the Bahamas.
Working out in the gym, attending a Zumba class or practicing Kathak are some of the ways I try to keep myself fit. In the remainder of my spare time I try to catch up on some reading or some good shows on the TV. Presently revisiting Ayn Rand's 'The Fountainhead'.

The other day I was helping my cousin complete a beautiful picture puzzle. We were done with every piece in the right place, but there was crucial piece missing, obviously rendering it incomplete. That's when I realized my life is pretty comparable to that picture puzzle. Now, the question I have for you - are you that missing piece?,"Looking for a charming young man, preferrably Hindu and in United States. I am an independent sort of a person with a positive outlook towards life.  I am open minded and take up life as it comes and dona??t like to customize it. My friends appreciate me for my good sense of humor and high values towards traditional and cultural ethics. 
A distance should be maintained between our personal and professional lives. I completely believe in this and follow it in my life. This is why I am happy in my professional life which has helped me grow as an individual. By profession I am an educationist in an online coaching Institute. In future I want to be in the same field and want to expand myself. 
I have a supportive and understanding family and I give them the utmost preference in my life. I have a sweet mother who is a teacher by profession and a liberal father who is working as a consultant. I also have a lovely sister who is married and well settled in her married life. 
After completing my school I did my higher education from Delhi University and did BA from there and MA from IGNOU. 
I have very few people who are close to me and they are my best friends. I like to watch movies and travel with them. Whenever I am free I like to read books of my interest and listen to music.,"I want a life partner in my life who has a good sense of humor with a broader way of analyzing and judging life. He should be an intellectual person so that both of us can share good vibes.
He should be well qualified and must belong to the same professional background as mine. Further, he should be well settled so that both of us can lead a problem free married life.

My parents and my concern will be towards the family background of my life partner. He should be decent in life as well as in his thoughts. I would prefer a man from the Delhi/NCR region with a well mannered family.
I am ready to share my life with him if he is like the one I am looking for.

column1:
I describe myself as a simple and friendly person with a very cheerful nature. I cannot see anyone sad so I always try and make other people happy. My jovial nature is enjoyed by everyone and they really like my company.  I easily get along with people and adapt myself in any situation. 
Presently I am working as a corporate planner in Unilever, London. In the upcoming time I want to see myself as a successful person and want to make my parents feel proud of me. Every day I work hard with an aim to attain a reputable position in my profession.  
My weakness is that I am very emotional. And my strengths are that I can easily adapt myself according to the situations and I am also a family oriented girl.
I am a homely person and always stay close to my family as I really respect and love them. They are my real support and without them I cannot even think of living my life. My family includes a lovely mother who is a homemaker and has sacrificed a lot for us and a responsible father who has taken retirement from his profession. In addition to this, I have a sister who is a doctor by profession.  
I was a good student of my school and performed well in my class. I have also received many complements from my teachers for this. After completing my school I did PGDBM from Narsimunji, Mumbai.
Friends are always there for us as they laugh with us in our happy times and become one of our biggest supports when we are sad. In my free time I meet up my friends and watch movies with them. I event go to visit different destinations with them. Listening to music refreshes me and gives me time for myself therefore I also love to listen to music.,"Marriage is one of the most beautiful relations of all. If you always have your partner with you at all times of joy and sorrow then it is a divine blessing of god.

I want a person in my life that is simple and decent in nature as well as in his thoughts. He should be family oriented so that when he gets married to me then he should easily mingle with my family. I will reciprocate him positively by accepting his family.

He should be well educated and must have a decent way of living life. I have no choices in the profession of my husband as he can be from any field. I just want him to be well settled so that after marriage we dona??t struggle to fulfill the basic necessities of our life.

His family background would be a major concern for my family as it will be significant for them to see me entering a well mannered and decent family. I would prefer a man from India or London. I am ready to get settled with him if he is just the way I want him to be.

column1:
Hi

To begin with, i would like to say that i basically belive, to live and let live others, i like indian culture and our value system especially. the close bonding that we share with our family, here i would like to state that i am blessed to have one such family. My family comprises of Dad, a Central Government Employee, Younger Bro who finished his B. E. and is working & my dad's eldest sis, i. e. my aunt. I lost my mom when i was quite young. I am very attached to my family. My brother being my best critic and i owe all my success to my aunt and dad.

I am very expressive and direct, very sensitive & glad that i am this way, as i am usually liked by everyone for this ( I owe this to my Psychology degree). I tend to give a lot of importance to emotions and the need to express them, i personally feel this was present in the indian culture but we are losing now as all of us are hard pressed for time and getting materialistic. I am very matured by my thinking and prefer others also to be this way.
Oh ya... i am ambitious but not at the cost of losing a family.... so i am highly family based. So i balance between my career and family and expect my man to do the same. I am currently doing my Ph. D in management.
Looking out for a person who is also equally sensitive and expressive of emotions, who tends to value the importance of others emotions even if he does not necessarily agree with it. He should be sensibile and oriented to the needs of family, should be achievement oriented but have the morals not to stamp on to others shoes to be successful. It would be great if he too has a blend of likingness for Indian culture and traditions and the modern views.
I would expect him to move into my family and be a part of my family and not just in my life, i vow to be the same towards him. I basically aim at two families getting together and not just two individuals.
I have a mental block towards alcohol and smoking so prefer my man not have those habits.,"Looking out for a person who is also equally sensitive and expressive of emotions, who tends to value the importance of others emotions even if he does not necessarily agree with it. A Libran born at 12.30 pm on 28th September, 1980,  in a Brahmin family in Bhagalpur. We belong to "Bhardwaj Gotraa". I am 5.3 tall and weigh 50 kg.

My early childhood was spent in Assam. Schooling in St. Stephens, Tinsukia, SSPM Chiplun and Bhawans School, Bharuch.
Graduation took me to BMCC; Pune where I did commerce and then further pursued Post Graduation Diploma in Management from IIMM [2003].  First job and financial freedom came with Tata Infomedia where I worked for about a year. Better career prospects made me shift to ICICI Prudential where I spent four years making my way to Sales Manager. Next jump and promotion came with my joining Bajaj Allianz in October, '08. This is a challenging job and my responsibility as Regional Manager spans across the country with base in Mumbai. I do travel to various cities at least twice a month.
I quite enjoy my present job but would like to be in the financial sector in the years ahead. My total financial remunerations adds to six digit in a year.

Though working in Mumbai is hectic I do find time to indulge in weekend outing with family and long long drives. Reading preference is eclectic, inspirational and self motivating text being the current flavor. Good movies, music, both film and Indian classical is top on my activity list. Games, adventure sports and travel to exotic places is on my wish list. I value my family and am proud of our culture and traditions. Firmly believe in marriage and permanent relationships, and would happily give away all for a happy home and family.  Natural surrounding, company of people with substance and indulgence in activities where I can contribute as a person is what I cherish and long for.

My family consists of my parents and one sister and a brother. Sister is elder, engaged and working as a HR Manager in Patni Computers. Younger brother, a management post graduate has started his career with Ballarpur Industries, Delhi.  My father is a Chartered Accountant and is with Indorama Cements, Mumbai. His earlier jobs took us to Assam, Orissa, Gujarat and finally Maharashtra, where we now have a permanent base in Panvel [Mumbai]. Our ancestral home is in Rajasthan, though my grand parents lived in Bhagalpur. My mother's family is mostly settled in Assam. column1:
First, the cliches (i mean... who would say bad things about themselves anyway?).... Happy, calm, focused, trusting, fun-loving (if you cant laugh... then whats the point?), extroverted, love nature, hate concrete, need some 'alone-time' occasionally, structured, adaptable, curious... Things that are close to my heart are family, honesty (esp. to yourself about your own vulnerabilities), happiness, being spiritual and being "into" life - both the ups and the downs. ... what i believe now after seeing hard times is " what's the use of worrying?? it never was worthwhile, so pack your troubles in your kit-bag and smile, smile and smile"

Note:- I'm currently in United States for vacations till August 2011.,"i looking for

someone who I can share my life with. That means love, fun, sharing solem moments, teasing, fighting (of course, i expect to lose) - really just someone with whom I can grow and share everything thats in my heart without giving a second thought... someone who not only understands my words but my silence... I'm definitely looking for someone who can talk to me about anything, someone that I can have long conversations with about both important and meaningless things, someone who approaches life with an unspoken grace and a gentle optimism yet knows that the road can be hard and tough. I`m looking for a best friend who I can really be there for throughout the good times and the bad. Oh, and someone to watch the sunsets with... But hey, chemistry and that special ""x-factor"" are really hard to quantify in a few words (or even in a few thousand) and don't even come close to describing the depths and intricacies of who someone really is...
so if u r smiling hit the contact button and make a friend
Otherwise  best of luck to everyone that pursues their dreams in life without endangering the dreams of others

Being the youngest of all in her company, she is not only adored extremely among her co-workers but also very fondly treated by her seniors as well due to the kind of sincerity she puts into her job. On holidays, she goes out with us, her friends and at times simply stays at home reading books, watching TV or painting. She is not a regular cook but occasionally she makes these full course meals, which i must say she makes even better than her mom. I believe, one day she is definitely going to open her own chain of food joints, because cooking happens to be one of her most secretly favorite activity.,It is difficult to measure up a human being and say that we want a smart/intelligent/sincere/humorous/caring life partner for her. column1: Hello I am a God fearing person and spiritual. I believe nothing happens without His blessings. I feel at the end of the day it is important to be happy from within. I believe in giving happiness to people around me. I feel carrying on grievances and hurt is wasting energy in life. I love to be active, do well for everyone around me in whatever ways I can. I would love to have a partner who would believe in the same and would extend his kind support in the worst of times. I believe strongly in a few things; they are IF YOU REST YOU RUST, ALL THAT IS BEAUTIFUL MAY NOT BE GOOD, BUT ALL THAT IS GOOD IS ALWAYS BEAUTIFUL. IF YOU ARE UNHAPPY, IT IS BECAUSE YOU HAVE ORGANIZED YOURSELF FOR THE SAME. NO ONE MAKES YOU UNHAPPY. I AM THE PERSON WHO WOULD ALWAYS SEARCH FOR THE OPEN DOORS AND NOT BANG ON THE CLOSED DOORS IN LIFE AND BLEED. I am a very frank person; believe in doing things on time, very punctual. And I take life as it comes by. No anxieties of the past and no anxieties of the future either, make me live happy in PRESENT. I am a very open person, who would consider everybody's opinion and believe in respecting the individuality in each one. I wish to balance my family and professional life in a harmonious way. I wish to give an equal weight age to both my family and profession. And yes as far as ambitions go, well I would ascertain myself globally in the field I shall pursue. But again striking a fine balance with family and career. I love kids. I feel they make living worthwhile. I believe in loyalty, honesty and self effort. I wish to pursue my further study in Neurology as I feel it is a very fascinating subject. I love traveling, listening to music, meeting new people, learning new things. I vow to be fully supportive to Him in all matters. I would love to have medico/non medico, no particular preference but yes I would wish to have someone who has really seen life in its all forms, who is not very judgmental, sensitive to others, supportive and believe in A?WEA? as I said earlier.,,I am the only child.My father is a doctor..a practicing anaesthetist and mother has done MSC in pharmacology and is a housewife. ,27 to 33,29 May 1980,,India,Jamnagar,Athletic,Athletic,,Lohana,,,,Fair ,Doesn't Matter,Self,MD/ MS (Medicine),"33 yrs, 5ft 5in,
